race.comment: Keen to stick with POINT BARROW (7) who was an outstanding winner when last seen at Caulfield, getting a mile back off a strong tempo but rattling home with enormous sectionals to get up as a well-backed favourite. Back to 1100m is the slight niggle but the wide draw down the straight looks perfect for her to wind up. AKAYSHA (9) continues to race well in handy races, taking on the older mares last time at Caulfield in the Alinghi Stakes and running well for a narrow fourth. Her fresh placing to My Gladiola (Coolmore 2nd to Tentyris) over this track and trip reads very well. SURF'S UP (10) was run down by POINT BARROW last time and has to be a chance, while TRES MAGNIFIQUE (17) had no luck there and has had no luck since. Barrier one the niggle for her but the straight should suit.
